## Learned Rules

<!-- Append below; same format as 000-core-rules.mdc. Number sequentially within this file. -->

1. [UX] Before introducing new UI colors or spacing patterns in `apps/web`, read **`docs/design-system.md`** and extend **`apps/web/src/app/globals.css`** tokens instead of ad-hoc hex/`zinc-*` — keeps LocalPDF branded and consistent for end users.
2. [DATA] Never pass the canonical `ArrayBuffer` stored for `pdf-lib` directly to `pdfjs.getDocument({ data })` without copying (e.g. `bytes.slice(0)`) — pdf.js can transfer/detach the buffer to the worker, breaking later `PDFDocument.load` with “detached ArrayBuffer”.
3. [ARCH] Deduplicate `pdfjs.getDocument` per document id when many thumbnails mount at once — concurrent loads can each call `setCachedPdfJsDocument`, destroying the previous `PDFDocumentProxy` and breaking other tiles; use one in-flight `Promise` per id. Treat `RenderingCancelledException` from cancelled renders as non-fatal; keep the `<canvas>` mounted so retries still have a ref.
